# GitHub App installation tokens compatibility

GitHub is rolling out a new **stateless (JWT-style)** format for GitHub App installation tokens.  
This file documents how Sentinal‑Cardio remains compatible during and after the rollout.

## Token formats

GitHub App installation tokens now come in two formats:

- **Old (stateful) tokens**
  - Short, opaque strings
  - No dots (`.`) in the value

- **New (stateless) tokens**
  - Start with `ghs_`
  - Much longer (~520 characters)
  - Contain two dots (`.`), similar to JWTs
  - Must still be treated as **opaque** (do not decode)

## Temporary per-request override header

GitHub provides a temporary header to control which token format is returned from:

`POST /app/installations/:installation_id/access_tokens`

Header:

- `X-GitHub-Stateless-S2S-Token: enabled`  
  → Force **new stateless** token format

- `X-GitHub-Stateless-S2S-Token: disabled`  
  → Force **old opaque** token format

If the header is omitted, GitHub’s normal rollout behavior applies.

### Example: Requesting an installation token (curl)

```bash
curl -X POST \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer <JWT_FROM_APP_PRIVATE_KEY>" \
  -H "Accept: application/vnd.github+json" \
  -H "X-GitHub-Stateless-S2S-Token: enabled" \
  https://api.github.com/app/installations/<installation_id>/access_tokens
